** About IT&C **   
We are a leading TSP (Technology Solutions Provider) with a national presence
going through massive growth.

Our offices are in Sydney, Central Coast, Melbourne, Gold Coast, Brisbane, and
Bundaberg.

We are looking for an experienced ** Project Engineer ** with excellent
customer service skills to join our ** Brisbane ** team.

You must have the ability to resolve a range of issues for our diverse
customer base across a range of technologies, while delivering a personal
touch.

This role is a mix of pre-sales, technical project management and project
delivery - supporting our Managed Services customer base.

** About the Role **   
As the ** Project Engineer ** , you will be responsible for building your own
day around client meetings, project scoping & delivery of multiple concurrent
projects.

You will focus on pre-sales, designing, planning and deployment of
infrastructure projects for our QLD and National clients.  
  
  
** Main Duties & Responsibilities **

  * Working with relevant stakeholders to design solutions using the IT&C product/service stack (Microsoft Cloud/Azure, Sophos, Datto, HPE, Aruba) 
  * Provide pre-sales design, consulting and assistance to Technical Account Managers and Sales team 
  * In collaboration with key team members, ensure the project delivers a smooth transition to front-line and operational support teams so that impacts to service delivery and other BAU activities are minimised 
  * Build project plans, manage and deliver projects 
  * Final (L3) support escalation point for client requests and support team 
  * Providing all levels of support services via ConnectWise Manage PSA & RMM Systems 
  * Document clients' infrastructure and business systems in ITGlue 
  * Train & mentor IT&C Group Support and Project team (training through ticket escalation) 
  * Maintaining vendor certifications (e.g. Microsoft, Sophos, Datto - to name a few) 

  
** Required Skills **

  * Proven experience in managing the end-to-end delivery of concurrent complex IT projects, including planning, scheduling, and resource management 
  * Proven experience migrating business systems to the Microsoft 365/Azure ecosystem 
  * Proven experience managing people/teams for the purpose of project delivery 
  * Previous experience in an MSP project delivery role is essential (min. 5 years) 
  * Microsoft 365 ecosystem (setup of new tenants, migration projects, etc) 
  * Microsoft Azure infrastructure (design and deployment) 
  * Microsoft Endpoint Manager/Autopilot (design and deployment) 
  * Windows Server (design and deployment) 
  * High-level understanding of Networking Technologies (DHCP/DNS/LAN/VLAN/WLAN/WAN) 
  * Experience with Antivirus/XDR Technologies (Sophos/Microsoft Defender XDR desirable) 
  * Strong documentation skills 
  * Ability to communicate technical and non-technical concepts to a wide range of stakeholders 
  * Experience with ConnectWise PSA/RMM/Project setup preferred 
  * Ability to build team culture focused on a successful delivery   

** Personal Attributes **   

  * A valid QLD driver’s license and your own roadworthy vehicle 
  * Current Microsoft 365/Azure certifications - required 
  * Formal project management accreditation/qualification – desirable 
  * Exceptional communication and proven stakeholder management experience 
  * Exceptional attention to detail, time management skills and strong project management discipline 
  * Ability to work autonomously and within a team 
  * Eager to continuously grow and improve technical skills 
  * Consistently presentable and punctual 

  
** Benefits **

  * Personal development - ongoing training around and industry certifications 
  * Exposure to a multitude of sites and network environments/technologies within SME, Enterprise and Government 
  * Exposure to various projects and deployments 
  * Great team environment and culture 
  * Work-life balance flexibility (WFH, office, client sites) 

